This project depends on the following open-source libraries:

- Mastodon.py (MIT) — https://github.com/halcy/Mastodon.py
- requests (Apache 2.0) — https://github.com/psf/requests
- python-dotenv (BSD-3-Clause) — https://github.com/theskumar/python-dotenv
- thefuzz (MIT) — https://github.com/seatgeek/thefuzz
- python-Levenshtein (GPL-2.0) — https://github.com/maxbachmann/python-Levenshtein

Note: python-Levenshtein is licensed under GPL-2.0. It is an optional runtime
dependency used to speed up fuzzy matching. If GPL-2.0 is incompatible with
your use case, you may remove it from requirements.txt — thefuzz will fall back
to a pure-Python implementation automatically.
